headline: Cisco’s New AI Partner Push And What It Might Mean For NasdaqGS CSCO
summary: Cisco Systems (NasdaqGS:CSCO) introduced its 360 Partner Program, aimed at supporting partners building AI solutions and services. The company announced new collaborations, including a Wi Fi 7 deployment with Georgetown University and an AI and cloud compute partnership with Sharon AI and Digital Alpha in Asia Pacific. Cisco sits at the center of networking, security, and collaboration technology. Any shift in how it works with partners can matter for how its products reach customers. The...
